<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="49" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,898,1427]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
Shoots 
<quantity box="[286,375,1014,1040]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" unit="cm" value="3.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.0">1–5 cm</quantity>
long. 
<emphasis box="[451,532,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Leaves</emphasis>
(2-)3(–4) lobed, lobes mostly acute, lacking cilia on the postical margin (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dumortier" authorityYear="1835" baseAuthorityName="Martius" baseAuthorityYear="1817" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Lophozia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="attenuata">N. attenuata</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[290,455,1053,1078]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Anastrophyllaceae" genus="Neoorthocaulis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="binsteadii">N. binsteadii</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
) or with 1–3 cilia (
<emphasis box="[713,1065,1053,1078]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicName box="[713,854,1053,1078]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Anastrophyllaceae" genus="Neoorthocaulis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="floerkei">N. floerkei</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[869,1065,1053,1078]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Anastrophyllaceae" genus="Neoorthocaulis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="hyperboreus">N. hyperboreus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
). Trigones small to bulging. Underleaves lacking or large and bifid (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Buch" authorityYear="1933" box="[659,800,1092,1117]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Anastrophyllaceae" genus="Orthocaulis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[659,800,1092,1117]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Orthocaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
small and unlobed). Gemmae absent or green to red. Dioicious. Perianth longly exserted, cylindrical, plicate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,898,1427]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,333,1168,1194]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Etymology</emphasis>
:—This genus consists of most species that 
<bibRefCitation author="Buch, H." box="[867,1017,1169,1195]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" pagination="282 - 297" refId="ref3227" refString="Buch, H. (1933) Vorarbeiten zu einer Lebermoosflora Fenno-scandias. I. Ein Versuch zur Aufspaltung der Gattungen Lophozia Dum. und Sphenolobus Steph. Memoranda Societatis pro Fauna et Flora Fennica 8 &quot; 1932 &quot;: 282 - 297." type="journal article" year="1933">Buch (1933)</bibRefCitation>
included in his genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Buch" authorityYear="1933" box="[1296,1436,1169,1194]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Anastrophyllaceae" genus="Orthocaulis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1296,1436,1169,1194]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Orthocaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except the species lectotypifying that genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,898,1427]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,257,1246,1272]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Note</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authority="R. M. Schust." authorityName="R. M. Schust." box="[294,757,1246,1272]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Lophozia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="section" section="Attenuatae">
<emphasis box="[294,403,1247,1272]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Lophozia</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[474,601,1247,1272]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Attenuatae</emphasis>
R.M.Schust.
</taxonomicName>
is described as belonging to subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Buch" authorityYear="1933" box="[1225,1365,1247,1272]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Anastrophyllaceae" genus="Orthocaulis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1225,1365,1247,1272]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Orthocaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The genus/subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Buch" authorityYear="1933" box="[349,492,1285,1310]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Anastrophyllaceae" genus="Orthocaulis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[349,492,1285,1310]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Orthocaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is typified by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kitagawa, N." box="[670,873,1285,1311]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" pagination="76 - 118" refId="ref3749" refString="Kitagawa, N. (1963) A revision of the family Marsupellaceae of Japan. Journal of the Hattori botanical laboratory 26: 76 - 118." type="journal article" year="1963">Kitagawa (1963)</bibRefCitation>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Buch" authorityYear="1933" baseAuthorityName="Kaalaas" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[943,1098,1285,1310]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Anastrophyllaceae" genus="Orthocaulis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="atlanticus">
<emphasis box="[943,1098,1285,1310]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">O. atlanticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but this apparently escaped Schuster who typified it with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Konstantinova &amp; Vilnet" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Hubener" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[497,643,1324,1349]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Anastrophyllaceae" genus="Schljakovia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="kunzeana">
<emphasis box="[497,643,1324,1349]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">O. kunzeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Schuster then included 
<taxonomicName authority="(H. Buch) Schiffner (1901: 46)" authorityName="Schiffner" authorityPageNumber="46" authorityYear="1901" baseAuthorityName="H. Buch" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Lophozia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="atlantica" subGenus="Orthocaulis">
<emphasis box="[932,1319,1324,1349]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Lophozia (Orthocaulis) atlantica</emphasis>
(H.Buch) 
<bibRefCitation author="Schiffner, V." box="[151,394,1362,1388]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" pagination="75 - 130" refId="ref4381" refString="Schiffner, V. (1901) Kritische Bemerkungen uber die europaischen Lebermoose mit Bezug auf die Exemplare des Exsiccatenwerkes, Hepaticae Europeae exsiccatae 1 (1 - 56). Sitzungsberichte des Deutschen Naturwissenschaftlich- Medicinischen Vereins fur Bohmen &quot; Lotos &quot; in Prag 49: 75 - 130." type="journal article" year="1901">Schiffner (1901: 46)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in his new section 
<taxonomicName box="[628,757,1363,1388]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Lophozia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="section" section="Attenuatae">
<emphasis box="[628,757,1363,1388]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Attenuatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
making it an illegitimate name according to Art. 
<quantity box="[1353,1436,1362,1388]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6134" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" unit="in" value="22.1">22.1 in</quantity>
ICBN (
<bibRefCitation author="McNeill, J. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Burdet, H. M. &amp; Demoulin, V. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; Nicolson, D. H. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Silva, P. C. &amp; Skog, J. E. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Turland, N. J." box="[236,473,1401,1427]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" pagination="146" refId="ref4102" refString="McNeill, J., Barrie, F. R., Burdet, H. M., Demoulin, V., Hawksworth, D. L., Marhold, K., Nicolson, D. H., Prado, J., Silva, P. C., Skog, J. E., Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Turland, N. J. (2006) International Code of Botanical Nomenclature (Vienna Code) adopted by the Seventeenth International Botanical Congress Vienna, Austria, July 2005. Regnum Vegetabile 146." type="journal article" year="2006">
McNeill 
<emphasis box="[343,402,1401,1426]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
